  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Milling Machine Operator",
  "description": "<p>Job Description & Requirements</p><p><strong>Job Overview</strong></p><p>We are looking for an experienced Senior Milling Machine Operator to set up, operate, and maintain milling machines for high-precision components. This role ensures product quality, machine efficiency, and supports junior operators in daily machining tasks.</p><h3><strong>Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li>Set up and operate conventional milling machines, conventional lathe machines according to technical drawings.</li><li>Perform machine adjustments, tooling setup, and operation.</li><li>Inspect parts using precision measuring tools to ensure tolerances are met.</li><li>Troubleshoot machining issues and improve production efficiency.</li><li>Maintain machine cleanliness, safety, and basic preventive maintenance.</li><li>Guide and support junior machinists.</li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li>Certificate/Diploma in Precision Engineering or Machining Technology.</li><li>2+ years of conventional milling experience in precision engineering.</li><li>Strong blueprint reading and GD&T knowledge.</li><li>Good teamwork, communication, and attention to detail.</li><li>Experience with conventional lathe machining is a plus.</li></ul><p><strong>Aurora Asia (21C0671) | Stephanie Luan (R21100585)</strong></p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
